< Review>
Was downtown Gilroy looking for a place to eat, when out of the corner of my eyes I caught the  tacos del Guero sign. After flipping a U-ee we pulled into a fairly sizable parking lot that has plenty of parking just for their business.
There is some nice signage on the building.
As I walked inside I noticed the left side where all the seating is was blacked out.
they are definitely a mom and pop ‚Äúask the locals‚Äù kind of place.
. I asked the lady if she had a menu and she said no  however she spent the time to let me know what kind of meats and food they served.
The ladies behind the counter were super nice and even smiled when I took  pictures.
Wifey needs to use the rest room, they were nice enough to let her use it, even With this crazy ‚ÄúCh-eye-na‚Äù virus going on.
They have condiments underneath a steel closed lid container that you can access yourself.
I ordered a super burrito with L Pastore and wifey ordered three street tacos one with Carnitas and two with steak. They will give you salsa red, green or both on the side, The green was super flavorful with very little heat, the red was more for us spicy loving people but I felt the flavor was not quite as developed as the green.
When I tore open my burrito the first thing I noticed was the shell had been toasted nicely and actually had a really good flavor the burrito had beans, rice, juicy help Pastor meet, with whole cut avocado slices inside. Adding the green salsa added a whole ‚Äúnother‚Äù dimension to the flavor.
The price point is actually really good at this place at $9:50 per person including drinks.
Bottom line..... good food, service and price. ‚ÄúI‚Äôll be back‚Äù<//Review>

< review>
I share this from my own experience. This was my fur baby's primary vet  for the last 5 years. Last year around October I notice my baby was coughing and  his breathing was a bit off. I took him to the vet about 5-6 times from October to December. The vet although very nice simply stated he had allergies, but never did any lab work or any exams. Which i now wish i should have pushed for, but my ignorance in this case won. The last time I took him in December he was just not well. The vet simply stated he was overweighed (which in reality was liquid retention). That same night around almost 1am I had to rush him to an emergency animal hospital because he wasn't breathing well. I hospitalized my baby for about a week and I thought he would come home, but he was diagnosed with pneumonia and he didn't get better. Sadly i had to make the most painful decision of my life to let him go because he was just suffering and no amount of treatment was helping. He was so attached to me and i know that he was scared and wondering where i was and with covid i was unable to even visit him. Anyways I finally had the courage to write this with tears and guilt because even though I know It was my responsibility to have have taken him somewhere else for a second opinion, I write this in hopes of helping someone.  Yes the vet there is kind but I think they have to many clients and cant provide the best care. I write this because if you have a similar experience please take your fur baby's somewhere else for a second opinion honestly the cost is the least important thing. It's been a month and a half now and I still cant manage my loss.< /review>

<userid>102810404558492134962</userid>< review>
As I saw in other reviews, don't let the looks of the building deceive you. Dr. K is a kind, generous, caring doctor. He cares about his patients and also their owners. It is worth being patient with the COVID19 safety protocols. Dr. K is working 6-7 days a week to try to meet the demand caused by clinics limiting their intakes due to COVID. Just bring a book to read or podcast to listen to in the car while you wait your turn. My dog's biopsy cost almost half of what I normally pay in Mammoth Lakes and Dr. K alerted me that my dog's labs were off, recommended I get her on supplements, and scheduled a follow up to try to figure out why her liver function is off. Finding someone who is 'pro-active' is so rare these days. The community is lucky to have such a wonderful human being to care for their pets!</review>

<review>First off I would like to say that although this facility may be small, the decor outdated, and there are at times a wait, Dr. Kiaei (Dr. K) and the veterinary assistants always provide utmost care for my pets. Dr. K is knowledgeable, confident, and goes above and beyond when caring for my furry ones. Mercy, one of their receptionists, always knows me and my cats by name. She is personable, patient, and always willing to help answer my questions.

Over the years I have brought numerous (12+) cats/kittens to be spayed and neutered by Dr. K. They kept the kitties there for a few hours after surgery to make sure they were recovering well. There were no complications at home and everyone healed nicely.

I've gone to several veterinary facilities in the surrounding area and by far they are the most affordable. You can't beat the level of care, knowledge, and dedication Dr. K has for his patients. One of my kitties was very ill and needed to be hospitalized for several days. Dr. K would drive back and forth from his home to the hospital several times throughout the night to administer medication, check her IV line, and make sure my little girl was doing alright. How many non-emergency facilities have a Veterinarian this dedicated? Most places would send you to an emergency veterinary clinic for overnight care which costs an arm and a leg. Honestly, I'm not sure how Dr. K got any sleep during this time, but I am grateful he kept me up to date with her progress and was there to care for her.

Like most places sometimes there is a wait. As a pet owner and someone who frequents medical offices, understanding that emergencies occur and need to be seen ASAP should be recognizable. If I know I need to be somewhere I schedule an appointment either as the first appointment of the day, or the first appointment right after lunch. They do their best to keep on schedule while trying to accommodate those pets who need to be seen sooner. It's easier to understand when your pet has been in a position for needing urgent care.

Overall I recommend San Gabriel Animal Hospital to anyone looking for affordable care and a Veterinarian dedicated to his profession and the well-being of his patients.</review><pics>None</pics>< resp>
None</resp>

<review>I lovED this place....emphasis on the past tense. Frankly, I know they do not need my patronage because they are never NOT busy. They are so busy, they do not have time to call in prescriptions or to correct a wrong.

Dr told me that he would call in a prescription to the Alhambra Costco and did not. (Meds were for my paralyzed dog due a herniated disc that occurred 48 hrs previously.) I found out my prescription was not there only when I arrived at the pharmacy, and by then, the office was closed, so I fought 2 hour-plus traffic for nothing!!! Then Mercy called me the next day, never referencing my voice message or apologizing for the inconvenience. She told me she had just called the Monterey Park Costco. I asked for it to be sent to the one in Alhambra. She told me that she would.  Then, on a Saturday night, moments before the pharmacy would close, again, after fighting 2 hour plus traffic from the specialist in Tustin, battling the typical struggles to find parking at Costco on a Saturday, to barely make it to the pharmacy before it would close, I was told again that there was prescription waiting for me.

In tears and extremely frustrated (because I was also facing the decision to proceed with back surgery,) I left a message for someone to call me if they "respected me as a human and as a patron of their hospital." Two plus weeks later, my desperate cries for help were left unanswered.

Today, two weeks after the fact, I called to speak to someone. The phone rang many times. This was not typical. Usually, someone would answer within a 2 rings and place me on hold. This time was different; I knew Mercy was avoiding my call. How did I know? Because my number shows up when I call, that's when she DID NOT answer. I called right back with my number blocked and she picked up right away.

Of course she made excuses and "apologized" and fed me a line of "I never got your message"... but all of that disrespected me so much, knowing that she only picked up my call when she DID NOT see my number appear.

I am so very disappointed by the lack of professionalism, compassion and human decency by Mercy. She had previously treated me with such kindness and I had always looked forward to speaking with her. She calls everyone "mija" which made me feel like she cared, but now I know differently.< /review>< Pictures>
None<//Pictures>

< review>
I lovED this place....emphasis on the past tense. Frankly, I know they do not need my patronage because they are never NOT busy. They are so busy, they do not have time to call in prescriptions or to correct a wrong.

Dr told me that he would call in a prescription to the Alhambra Costco and did not. (Meds were for my paralyzed dog due a herniated disc that occurred 48 hrs previously.) I found out my prescription was not there only when I arrived at the pharmacy, and by then, the office was closed, so I fought 2 hour-plus traffic for nothing!!! Then Mercy called me the next day, never referencing my voice message or apologizing for the inconvenience. She told me she had just called the Monterey Park Costco. I asked for it to be sent to the one in Alhambra. She told me that she would.  Then, on a Saturday night, moments before the pharmacy would close, again, after fighting 2 hour plus traffic from the specialist in Tustin, battling the typical struggles to find parking at Costco on a Saturday, to barely make it to the pharmacy before it would close, I was told again that there was prescription waiting for me.

In tears and extremely frustrated (because I was also facing the decision to proceed with back surgery,) I left a message for someone to call me if they "respected me as a human and as a patron of their hospital." Two plus weeks later, my desperate cries for help were left unanswered.

Today, two weeks after the fact, I called to speak to someone. The phone rang many times. This was not typical. Usually, someone would answer within a 2 rings and place me on hold. This time was different; I knew Mercy was avoiding my call. How did I know? Because my number shows up when I call, that's when she DID NOT answer. I called right back with my number blocked and she picked up right away.

Of course she made excuses and "apologized" and fed me a line of "I never got your message"... but all of that disrespected me so much, knowing that she only picked up my call when she DID NOT see my number appear.

I am so very disappointed by the lack of professionalism, compassion and human decency by Mercy. She had previously treated me with such kindness and I had always looked forward to speaking with her. She calls everyone "mija" which made me feel like she cared, but now I know differently.</review>

< Review>
I am sure that everyone wants to give their pet the best medical treatment available and fight any battle and do every possible test and treatment. In the real world this just isn't possible for all of us. We have been to so many vets that hand you this monster bill at the end of an appointment and one wonders what happened.

At SGAH they intuitively know just how far they need to go. For example our dog, Jack, is 12 yrs old and maybe it is not worth putting him through chemotherapy.

It's hard enough to make these types of decisions for a member of the family without any implied guilt trips. We are VERY happy to have found SGAH and we don't want to tell anyone because we don't want it to get too crowded....

I do know that we won't be searching for a new vet ever again.<//Review>

< UserId.>
113571692361314156513<//UserId.>
<username>Sierra<//username><Time>1519173441433< /Time><Rate>4< /Rate>< Text>
Living at Pegasus is overall a pretty good experience. I think given all the places in Downtown Los Angeles Pegasus ranks higher.
Moving in and Moving out is pretty easy, they have a very large freight elevator that makes it much easier than a lot of buildings.
The rooftop pool is definitely a huge bonus to living here. Not many places in Downtown Los Angeles have rooftop pools and views are great. There is also a BBQ area, restrooms, tv lounge area and gym on the roof.
Neighbors on the floor I lived on at least are really nice and very respectful. I've heard that isn't the case for all the floors, I guess it's just lucky. I would say there is a healthy mix of people that live there, some in their 40's-50's and others 20's -30's. They don't have a ton of mixers to meet neighbors but the ones they do have I always met a lot of people.
The cons are the elevators, but you'll find that with a lot of places, I swear a lot of buildings have elevator issues. But when there is only one elevator working you can wait up to 15 minutes until it comes to your floor or the lobby.
The best part about Pegasus is the concierge. Amal was fantastic, always professional, remembers all the residents, and really helpful. I know some people struggled with Management, I personally never did, but I suppose it probably depends on your problem.</Text>

<userid>104245721150398365433<//userid><user_name>Jonah Breslow<//user_name><time>1530976876704< /time>< rate>
1<//rate>
< text>
Thankfully, my one year lease has finally come to an end. When I first moved in, my roommate and I had issues with water temperature, light fixtures, a broken in-unit washer, and terrible noise from the trash truck very early in the morning almost every day. When you inform the property managers of any issue they always become defensive and attempt to place the blame on the tenant. Often they appeal to their "experience" with these issues or they simply argue that because Equity Residential is a publicly traded company that they, somehow, know more than you about your own situation. To top this off, the property managers/leasing office will do anything to charge you an additional hidden fee. For example, when you give notice to evacuate the property after your lease has terminated, the leasing office posts a note on your door which states, "ESTIMATED CHARGES DUE AT OR PRIOR TO MOVE-OUT," (original emphasis) and the charges include: prorated rent, utilities, miscellaneous charges, parking, etc. Naturally, it seems that you should be allowed to pay this all "at or prior to move-out." Of course, if you follow these directions, you will be charged a hefty late fee because in actuality, you have to pay on the first of the month. While the leasing office is technically not wrong in stating that we had to pay on the date that we agreed to in our lease, they try to obscure any contractual obligations by providing the tenants with conflicting information to force the tenants to pay a late fee because of technicalities. This is simply a telling example of how this building is managed.

I highly recommend not living at the Pegasus and looking elsewhere. This building is managed by a slimy leasing office that really only cares about making money off the tenants.</text>

<text>My honest and in-depth review of the Pegasus

the Pros
‚Ä¢	Rooftop pool/gym/hangout/BBQ area was one of the best features of Pegasus.
‚Ä¢	All the concierge and leasing agents were extremely helpful throughout our stay anytime we needed help (big ups to Amal, Avery, & Alex. I apologize for missing some other names!)
‚Ä¢	Can‚Äôt forget the maintenance guys either, they were always quick and extremely helpful!
‚Ä¢	The apartments are small (that‚Äôs just DTLA) but they are nice and set up well (minus the all-in-one washer/Dryer). The AC worked great for somebody that likes to keep it cold in their apartment.
‚Ä¢	Mixer events! I have never stayed anywhere that did this, but these were great, and we did make a few friends that have moved on from the Pegasus that we are still in touch with. Anybody that is not from LA knows how hard it is to make friends and having them in the same apartment as you make it easier to hang out!
‚Ä¢	These guys are pet friendly and extremely welcoming of them. I have found this to not to be common in places that even claim to be pet friendly.
‚Ä¢	Freight elevator is a godsend for moving in/out. This is not common but an amazing feature of this place.

The Cons
‚Ä¢	To start, I had scheduled an apartment walk and show up to see we are double booked (oldest trick in the book to put the sales pressure on). Well it worked because we were blinded by that glorious rooftop pool. We jumped into our apartment before taking a minute to consider other factors. (see below)
‚Ä¢	I will accept partial responsibility for this, but we were never clued in that the apartment we were moving into would have the new metro construction going on around the clock for the next year or so. would have been nice to get a heads up to potentially consider another area of the building.
‚Ä¢	The lighting in these apartments is pathetic even by California apartment standards. 2 terribly dim lights in the kitchen and dining room using some goofy bulb that can‚Äôt be swapped out with something better. Normally I wouldn‚Äôt write this item down but for an apartment that costs 2500+ dollars for a 1 bedroom I felt it belonged here.
‚Ä¢	The all-in-one washers and dryers got to go. They cannot keep up with people that go to work/gym/outs demand. 1 load can take up to 3 hours from beginning to end and your clothes will still wind up wrinkled. They have on site laundry, but this rant is long enough without diving into that mess. Again, probably not worthy of putting on a con list but I will refer you to my last statement regarding apartment cost.
‚Ä¢	Our neighbors F@*!&#g sucked. This isn‚Äôt necessarily the Pegasus‚Äô fault but after a 9+ months of off and on battle over banging a subwoofer loud enough so you cant even carry a conversation in your apartment without hearing (thun,thun,thun) rattle through your head, I can‚Äôt help but wish they would have done more with them. (I may be asking a bit much here, but it was the #1 reason we decided to leave).

I am still in the process of dealing with this item, but the deposit charges process has been a mess so-far. A week after my departure I was hit with nearly 900$ in ‚Äúdamages‚Äù. I am fully aware that I am not perfect and that there would be deductions, but this has felt excessive. The biggest mistake being that I requested an initial inspection to fix potential ‚Äúdamages‚Äù. The inspection was performed but I never received a follow up on these items. This has left me blindsided. I will update this review depending on the outcome. Take pictures, save your emails, and make copies of all paperwork you submit and receive. I am usually on these items but moving is stressful and when you have one day to move out and into a new spot its easy to miss those last critical steps. DO NOT wind up in the same position as me!

Overall, we liked our stay at the Pegasus Apartments. It‚Äôs unfortunate that our neighbors and this deposit dispute have left a sour taste in our mouth, but we did enjoy our time here before that started up. We liked living in downtown and would consider living there again in the future with a smarter approach.< /text>< Pics>

<user_name>deborah miller</user_name><date>1542033590048</date>< Rate>
1</Rate>
< Review>
We frequent Applebees at least once a week. We came to this location to meet our son and granddaughter for lunch because it's closer to his house.
The waiting area benches were missing a cushion so the Velcro on the exposed bench was full of hair and food crumbs.
Yuck.
We always get cheese sticks and the pub pretzels with the beer cheese dip.
Bummer. The pretzels had enough salt to qualify as a lick and the dip was enough for 2 pretzels, not 4.
The hubbs and I ordered the same thing, medium steak. When the meal came everyone got their food except for me. Unfortunately our server didn't put the order in for two steaks. When I did get my meal 15 minutes later it was a plate of blood, barely cooked steak.
So, I have to say we weren't exactly pleased with any of it. My granddaughters corn dog was burnt as well. They seemed to need the table so I just had my meal put in a box because everyone else was done eating.
It was just so disappointing.
My cats enjoyed the steak I brought home.
Will we eat at Applebee's again?
Probably so. This location?
No.</Review>

< Text>
First and foremost I want to start with I am a frequent Applebee‚Äôs customer. For the most part, I usually always have a great experience at the Moreno Valley Location great food, great service, and amazing atmosphere. My fellow coworkers and I often visit with a group of 20 or more and I have nothing but praise for that location.
I recently visited the Riverside location with a group of 6 adults and a toddler, because we wanted to switch it up a little bit, and how I wish I hadn‚Äôt. Firstly when appetizers got to our table (after a long wait) they were cold; we ordered a trio platter, with an additional spinach dip and boneless wings. However, the group did not want to fuss over it. Secondly, when dinners arrived, I ordered a Bourbon Street Chicken and Shrimp sizzling plate. I want to say it tasted amazing and juicy like it always does in the Moreno Valley location but it wasn‚Äôt even close. The potatoes were white, like recently cut barely cooked; cold and white. Another guest in my party ordered a Steak dinner, firstly her sides were wrong she requested potatoes and was brought vegetables, secondly she ordered her steak well done and it was brought at least medium well. We asked to get it fixed and the manager was brought to our table (she did not have a name tag). The manager could have just taken the steak back and cooked it through; however, she instead blamed the lighting at our table. There was other steaks ordered our table and there was more pink in our supposed ‚ÄúWell Done‚Äù steak then in our medium well steaks. She didn‚Äôt take the steak back until about ten minutes later. We didn‚Äôt want that experience to ruin our visit so we try to just stick out and maintain a positive attitude, but visit got worse. Our plates were finally returned, but all our guests had already finished eating.  Service was terrible, food was dry and flavorless. Food was clearly undercooked on the chicken and shrimp and manager noticed that. Worst Applebee‚Äôs experience.<//Text>
